summary: This document is an email chain from February 2020 between an FBI Special Agent and a records custodian (Michelle) regarding a subpoena for information related to Maxwell. The FBI is seeking booking records using email addresses but the initial searches yield no results, prompting requests for additional identifiers like credit card numbers or itinerary numbers.

persons.name: Michelle
persons.context: Employee responding to FBI subpoena requests for records related to Maxwell, indicating no bookings found with provided email addresses and requesting more identifying information.

persons.name: Special Agent M
persons.context: FBI agent from the New York Child Exploitation & Human Trafficking task force seeking records via subpoena related to Maxwell, providing email addresses for search.

connections.description: Law enforcement agent corresponding with records custodian to obtain information via subpoena regarding Maxwell.

events.title: Subpoena Received
events.description: A subpoena was received by the records custodian from the FBI regarding Maxwell.

events.title: Request for More Information
events.description: Michelle responds to the FBI stating that more identifying information (email addresses, credit card numbers, itinerary numbers) is needed to locate records, as initial search with provided emails yielded no bookings.

events.title: Final Search Result
events.description: Michelle confirms that a search using an additional email address provided by the FBI also yielded no records.

keyFacts: The FBI was actively investigating Maxwell in February 2020, seeking travel or booking records via subpoena.
Initial searches using provided email addresses for Maxwell yielded no booking records.
The records custodian required additional identifiers like credit card numbers or itinerary numbers to proceed, indicating challenges in locating records with just email addresses.
The correspondence shows a 30-day deadline for the FBI to provide more information or the matter would be considered closed.
